The '''Chief Firearms Officer''' or '''CFO''' is a Canadian official responsible for [[Possession and Acquisition Licence]]s, [[Authorization to Transport|authorizations to transport]], [[Authorization to Carry|authorizations to carry]], transfers of firearms, and gun show sponsorship approvals.  Each province has a CFO.

